Nigeria’s Gas Supply to Ghana Inconsistent, Guardian Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-28T08:25:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/nigeria-s-gas-supply-to-ghana-inconsistent-guardian-says.html
Nigeria ’s supply of liquefied
natural gas to power stations in  Ghana  has been inconsistent,
the  Guardian  newspaper reported, citing Ghanaian Energy Minister
Oteng Adjei.  Natural gas supplies has averaged 80,000 British thermal
units a day, since January, with a range of zero to 120,000, the
Lagos-based newspaper cited Adjei as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 